main event: Several witnesses reported seeing unidentified flying objects in Colorado Springs, Colorado, on 7 August 1964.
interesting points: The objects were observed for a duration of 2-8 minutes., A roll of undeveloped film was secured for further analysis., The presence of 5 witnesses was noted but their earlier reports on similar objects could not be confirmed., The objects did not show unrealistic flight patterns for known aircraft., Weather conditions at the time included high winds and thunderstorms, which may have contributed to the sightings.
witness description: The witnesses included civilians, one of whom was a carpenter.
